# Header and Page Actions Refactoring Walkthrough

I have successfully refactored the application's header architecture to move page-specific titles and actions from the global top header into the local page content. This creates a cleaner, more consistent, and flexible UI.

## Changes Made

### 1. Localized Headers and Actions
I refactored the following pages to remove the dependency on the global [PageHeader](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/klinikapp/frontend/src/lib/page-header.tsx#6-21) component and implement their own local headers:

- **Dashboard**: Greeting ("Merhaba, Ahmet! 👋") and "Düzenle" button are now local.
- **Patients (Hastalar)**: "Hastalar" title, patient count, "Yeni Hasta" and "Silinen Hastalar" buttons are unified in a local header.
- **Finance (Finans Yönetimi)**: "Finans Yönetimi" title and "Tahsilat" / "Gider" buttons are now local.
- **Statistics (İstatistikler)**: "İstatistikler" title and date/doctor filters are unified in a local header.
- **Messages (WhatsApp Inbox)**: "WhatsApp Inbox" title and subtitle are now local.
- **Settings (Ayarlar)**: "Ayarlar" title and description are now local.

### 2. Global Layout Cleanup
- **Simplified Global Header**: Modified `src/app/(app)/layout.tsx` to remove dynamic page titles and actions. The global top header now only contains global tools like "Hızlı Arama" (Quick Search) and Notifications.
- **Consistency**: All pages now follow a similar layout pattern where the page content starts with its own header section.

### 3. Verification
Verified the changes by running both the frontend and backend servers and navigating through each page:
- **Frontend**: http://localhost:3001
- **Backend**: http://localhost:3000

